title: Stearns County Sheriff's office says drugs, alcohol are factors in crash reported in St. Augusta, Minnesota
text:
Stearns County Sheriff's office says drugs, alcohol are factors in crash reported in St. Augusta, Minnesota
The Stearns County Sheriff's Office received a report of a crash before hearing a man scream that he was trapped in his vehicle. The man was transported to a hospital to be assessed for injuries.
ST. AUGUSTA
— A Dassel, Minnesota, man was taken to the St. Cloud Hospital to be assessed for injuries after his vehicle struck multiple trees before tipping over on its side.
According to a news release from the Stearns County Sheriff’s Office, a crash detection call with multiple impacts was made around 12:51 a.m. Wednesday, near Stearns County Road 136 in St. Augusta.
ADVERTISEMENT
Initially, dispatchers couldn’t hear anyone on the phone. Eventually, a male started screaming, stating that he was stuck in his vehicle.
Officers responded to the area and found a vehicle approximately 50 yards off the road in a heavily wooded area.
The driver of the vehicle was identified as 21-year-old Russel Parks, of
Dassel.
According to the release, Parks was traveling eastbound when his vehicle drifted off the road into a field before driving through multiple large trees. The vehicle eventually stopped, landing on the driver’s side.
St. Augusta Rescue was able to get Parks to climb out of the vehicle on the passenger side door. Parks was then taken to the St. Cloud Hospital to be assessed for injuries.
The crash remains under investigation by the Stearns County Sheriff's Office. It is believed that drugs and alcohol may be a factor, according to the release.
St. Augusta Fire and Rescue and Mayo Ambulance assisted the Stearns County Sheriff’s Office at the scene.
